es) and BHes. Two of these have\ncompanion masses between 1 and 3.5 $M_{\\odot}$, making them potential hosts of\nNSes (or lower mass main sequence stars). The other two are between 2.5 to 8\n$M_{\\odot}$ and 1.6 and 26 $M_{\\odot}$, respectively, and so are identified as\ncandidates for harbouring BH companions. However, unambiguous identification of\nthese systems as X-ray quiet compact object harbouring binaries requires follow\nup observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Oct 2022 16:33:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-31"}
